<!-- 11 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">09, Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Oven &amp; range repair, what people ask us</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does oven or range repair cost?</h3>
        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most residential oven and range repairs run between $150 and $350. A bake element or igniter replacement is toward the lower end. On professional-grade ranges like Wolf, Thermador, or Viking, parts costs are higher, we give you a full written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover?</h3>
        <p>All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. Same-day is our standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My oven heats but the temperature is way off, what's wrong?</h3>
        <p>The oven temperature sensor (probe) is almost always the culprit, when it fails or drifts, the oven under- or over-shoots consistently. We test the sensor first since it's the most common cause and a straightforward replacement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My gas burner won't ignite, is that a repair or can I fix it myself?</h3>
        <p>First check whether the burner cap and ports are clean, clogged ports from food spills are the most common reason a burner won't light. If clean and still won't ignite, the spark electrode, igniter module, or gas valve could be the issue. We carry these for the major brands.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My oven won't come out of self-clean mode and the door is locked, what do I do?</h3>
        <p>The door lock motor assembly has usually failed. Try cutting power at the breaker and waiting for a full cooldown, that sometimes releases it. If not, the door lock motor needs replacement. We carry these for the brands we see most across SoCal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Wolf, Thermador, and Viking ranges?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Wolf, Thermador, and Viking are three of the brands our technicians work on most frequently across SoCal. We source OEM parts directly from authorized suppliers for all three. LaCanche, BlueStar, Bertazzoni, ILVE, and Miele are also within our scope.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My oven bakes unevenly, is it the element or the sensor?</h3>
        <p>It could be either. A partially failed bake element heats unevenly across its length. A drifting temperature sensor causes the oven to cycle incorrectly throughout. We run a temperature test across multiple positions before concluding the cause.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>When does it make sense to repair vs replace an oven or range?</h3>
        <p>Rule of thumb: under 10 years old and the repair is under $400, fix it. Over 12 years old AND the repair is over $500, consider replacing, but pro-grade brands flip the math. Wolf, Thermador, Viking, La Cornue, Lacanche, BlueStar are almost always worth repairing through year 20+, replacement runs $8,000–$25,000+ and parts continue to be supported. We tell you straight which side of that line your unit falls on.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the 90-day warranty cover on oven repairs?</h3>
        <p>Every oven and range repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

